From 9b7c61a897941065c6c87d109e36668f93eb167a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 14:56:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] LU-20133 build: fix includes in posix_acl_to_xattr conftest

On Linux 7.0, header cleanups mean that <linux/posix_acl.h> no
longer gets a complete struct inode definition transitively and
struct mnt_idmap is not declared in scope. Including only
<linux/posix_acl_xattr.h> thus fails to compile and the configure
test returns a false negative.

Fix this by including <linux/fs.h> in the conftest
HAVE_POSIX_ACL_TO_XATTR_ALLOC_BUFFER.

Test-Parameters: trivial
Fixes: f85a7cf4c8d3 ("LU-20133 build: Compatibility updates for kernel v7.0")
Signed-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@thelustrecollective.com>
Change-Id: I4f6b170b40b2c0f46ccf857eda1a0e725c71ec78
---
 config/lustre-core.m4 | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/config/lustre-core.m4 b/config/lustre-core.m4
index 9ebaa5e4272a..4920574f6dfb 100644
--- a/config/lustre-core.m4
+++ b/config/lustre-core.m4
@@ -3639,6 +3639,7 @@ AC_DEFUN([LC_HAVE_FILEMAP_ALLOC_FOLIO_NUMA],[
 #
 AC_DEFUN([LC_SRC_HAVE_POSIX_ACL_TO_XATTR_ALLOC_BUFFER],[
 	LB2_LINUX_TEST_SRC([posix_acl_to_xattr], [
+		#include <linux/fs.h>
 		#include <linux/posix_acl_xattr.h>
 	],[
 		struct posix_acl *acl = NULL;
-- 
2.39.5

